snippet.textDisplay:
I feel a little bit sad that he only takes celebrity stylists into consideration...like..since he seems to have a really clear vision of what he wants, with that he could also just try to get in contact with an "usual" designer/stylist. They would still do a good job...it's not like they are worse just cause they take less money from you.

Celebrity stylists will always cost you a ton of money just because they are famous, not because their work is better than others. They would only design for you if it would be good promotion for them. Like dressing someone who goes on a red carpet and is famous. They do that because those have money, people look at them and everyone who interviews them will ask them "who are you wearing today?".

Just maybe think about getting a normal stylist/designer. Don't always just look for famous people....

snippet.textDisplay:
Ahh, I was laughing (lovingly) when I saw you sewing without putting the sewingfoot down, and thought poor poor machine xD
Really entertaining video, and to be a first try I think you did a great job!
I have been sewing since before I was 10 and I'm born the same year as Shane, if you really want to learn, I would recommend you go to a secondhand store and find pieces that are somewhat what you're looking for, wash them, get a seamripper and take those clothes apart to use them as guidence and patterns. It's really fun to figure out how things are made, good luck on your next sewing adventure!! =D
snippet.textOriginal:
